Sentencas: The Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-delta (SSC) fibers with embedded nano-Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 (SDC) particles are fabricated by electrospinning process using commercial SDC nanopowders and an SSC precursor gel containing polyvinyl alcohol (PVA) and aqueous metal nitrate.
Titulo: Fibrous mixed conducting cathode with embedded ionic conducting particles for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: After calcination at 800 degrees C, fibers with diameters ranged between 300 and 500 nm and well-developed SSC cubic-perovskite structure and SDC fluorite are successfully obtained.
Titulo: Fibrous mixed conducting cathode with embedded ionic conducting particles for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The calculated crystallite sizes of SSC and SDC are 20.78 and 45.35 nm, respectively.
Titulo: Fibrous mixed conducting cathode with embedded ionic conducting particles for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Over whole measured temperature ranges during the symmetrical cell test, the fiber composite cathode exhibits much lower polarization resistance than conventional powder composite cathodes.
Titulo: Fibrous mixed conducting cathode with embedded ionic conducting particles for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The polarization resistances are estimated to 0.06 and 1.23 Omega cm(2) for the fiber composites and 0.15 and 2.10 Omega cm(2) for the powder composites at 700 and 550 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Fibrous mixed conducting cathode with embedded ionic conducting particles for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The single cell with the fiber composite cathode shows much higher performances; its maximum power density is 380.5 mW cm(-2) at 550 degrees C and
Titulo: Fibrous mixed conducting cathode with embedded ionic conducting particles for solid oxide fuel cells
